  "body": "I've noticed that all `setState` calls that occur during a DOM handler get batched into the same render but calling `setState` outside of a handler can cause multiple renders. Is there a method I can call on a tree to tell it to enter the batching state?\n\n``` js\nvar tree = React.renderComponent(application, domNode);\ntree.inBatchContext(function() {\n  // Lots of setStates here\n});\n```\n",
